[[File:Fighting the Giant Mole.png|thumb|right|295px|A player fights the Giant Mole, the result of an accident involving [[Wyson]] and an ultra-growth potion.]]

The '''Giant Mole''' ('''''Talpidae wysonian'''''{{CiteNPC|npc=Natural history quiz|quote=The Giant Mole (Talpidae Wysonian)|loc=Varrock Museum|notes=West wing, Display case #7}}) is a [[boss]] found in the [[Mole Hole]], just under [[Falador Park]], alongside some [[Baby Mole (NPC)|baby moles]]. The Giant Mole's origin and creation are described as "a slight accident involving a bottle of ''[[Malignius Mortifer|Malignius-Mortifer]]'s-Super-Ultra-Flora-Growth-Potion''" when [[Wyson the gardener]] poured it on his plants.{{CiteNews|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/canoeing-zygomites-and-a-mole|title=Canoeing, Zygomites and a Mole!|newsdate=7 March 2006}}

The Giant Mole is accessed by digging with a [[spade]] on top of the park's mole hills. The tunnels are dark and the player will receive damage without a [[light source]]. An inextinguishable light source is recommended, such as a [[bullseye lantern]], [[abyssal lantern]], [[mining helmet]], [[bruma torch]], [[Kandarin headgear]], or [[Firemaking cape]]. Any [[candle]]s, [[torch]]es, or [[oil lamp]]s will be extinguished if she retreats within [[melee]] range. A [[tinderbox]] is needed to relight extinguished light sources. Furthermore, if a player has completed the quest [[Making Friends With My Arm]] and has lit the [[Fire of Eternal Light]] within the lair, they will no longer need to carry a light source in their inventory.

The Giant Mole is popular for its [[mole skin]] and [[mole claw]] drops, which can be traded to Wyson for [[Bird nest (Wyson)|unique bird nests]], and it is one of the only sources of consistent bird nests. Bird nests can be [[crushed nest|crushed]], which is an ingredient for making [[saradomin brew]]s.

==Fight Overview==
{{Main|Giant Mole/Strategies}}

The Giant Mole attacks with melee, which can deal up to 21 damage. She cannot path around obstacles, so she can be safespotted by players who are unwilling to take her attacks.

Upon reaching 50% of her health, every attack from the player has a 25% chance of causing her to burrow into the ground to another area in the lair, forcing players to chase her across the lair. This includes attacks that hit a 0, unless it is a magic attack that splashes.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1139454530406559744|date=14 June 2019|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/107093|archivedate=18 June 2019|quote=1/4 when its health is between 5% and 50%.}} This chance will remain until she falls below 5% of her health, after which she will no longer burrow away. When burrowing away, she will lose aggression. Having a [[Falador Shield 3]] or better will allow the player to track the mole in the lair while she is alive, making it easier to locate her. The burrow also has a chance to extinguish open [[light sources]], such as [[candle]]s and [[torch]]es, though closed sources like [[bullseye lantern]]s are safe from it.

The Giant Mole is immune to [[venom]], but is susceptible to [[poison]]. Poison damage does not force her to burrow, making it a great tool against her for shortening kill times. For [[ironmen]] (who typically do not have access to [[Poison++]] potions due to the high Herblore requirement), a great alternative is completing the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Trio]] quest and speaking to [[Tamayu]], who will reward the player with a [[rune spear (kp)]]. This karambwan-poison-coated weapon has the same poison strength as Poison(++).

